						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">exdeath wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Woot!  <br /><br />My first NES program!<br /><br />Code is a little messy, took some trial an error to figure out MMC3 / mapper 4.  <br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #%00000001<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $8000</div><br /><br />In this mode, 2k pages are swapped at pattern memory $0800-FFF.  What I learned via trial and error:<br /><br />1) The value written to $8001 to select the CHR-ROM page is the number of a page, not an address.  So 0 = the 1k page at PPU $0000, 1 = 1k page at $0400, 2 = 1k page at $0800 and so on.<br /><br />2) The page must be 2k aligned in the mode I'm using.  Selecting page 0 and 1 select the same 2k page from $0000-$07FF, page 2 and 3 = the same 2k page from $0800-$0FFF, etc.<br /><br /><a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/download/file.php?id=41" class="postlink">Attachment</a><br /></div><br /><br />Looking good!  Maybe try some dark tiles too, put them to the right of the walls.</div>

					
